r to the Provost and are tasked with teaching their apprentices to the best of their ability, as well as furthering their own fields of magic through research.\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0*Each Master may have multiple apprentices.\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0*There can be multiple masters for each type of magic appointed.-Selects prospective apprentices through exams determining potential magical aptitude, available for anyone to take. The Provost is also the proctor of these exams.\u00a0 \u00a0 *These exams also test general intelligence/literacy, though exceptions are made for individuals seen to have great magical \u00a0\u00a0\u00a0\u00a0potential when lacking in these areas.Warden of Magic ()-Responsible for maintaining the records of all known magic-users in Isra.-Oversees the operation The Enclave\u2019s scrying network to monitor Isran lands for any magical threats.-Commands a group of especially well trained Enclave Mages tasked with dealing with magical threats to Isra as well as guarding The Enclave.", "link_list": [], "image_list": [], "html": "<div style=\"text-align:center;\"><i>The Enclave is Isra's orders of mages. The Enclave is responsible for almost all things having to do with magic in the Isran Empire. This ranges from training battle-mages for the military and dealing with magical threats to the Empire to furthering magical research.</i></div>"}}